{"id":"project-LICHEN-ovdv","title":"lichen_link_set_epoch fails silently when lock fails","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/link/link_ctx.c
Lines: 246-256

lichen_link_set_epoch() returns void and fails silently if seq_lock() fails:

```c
void lichen_link_set_epoch(struct lichen_link_ctx *ctx, uint8_t epoch)
{
    if (ctx == NULL) {
        return;
    }
    if (seq_lock(ctx) != 0) {
        return;  // Silent failure - caller cannot detect
    }
    ctx->epoch = epoch;
    (void)seq_unlock(ctx);
}
```

On POSIX, pthread_mutex_lock can fail with EINVAL (uninitialized mutex) or EDEADLK (deadlock). If the lock fails, the epoch is not updated but the caller has no way to detect this.

Impact: Caller believes epoch was set when it was not. Could lead to nonce reuse if epoch change is critical for key rotation.

Severity: Low - on Zephyr, k_mutex_lock with K_FOREVER always succeeds. On POSIX, lock only fails due to programming errors. However, for safety-critical code, silent failures should be avoided.

Fix: Change return type to int and return error code on failure.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:47:08.81974Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:47:08.819777Z"}

